</style></head><body><h1 style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 7pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Peter <span class="s1">Backhouse</span></h1><p style="padding-top: 9pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: right;"><a href="mailto:peterbackhouse.sj@gmail.com">peterbackhouse.sj@gmail.com</a></p><h4 style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: right;">07402 191377</h4><p class="s2" style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: right;">15 Wilmington Square, WC1X 0ER</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"/><h2 style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 7pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Career</h2><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><h3 style="padding-left: 7pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">(2022)</h3><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><h3 style="padding-left: 5pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">(2021 - 2022)</h3><p class="s3" style="padding-top: 9pt;padding-left: 2pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Special Adviser <span style=" color: #7F7F7F;">Home Office</span></p><p style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 2pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">I served as a Special Adviser to the Security Minister. I was responsible for:</p><ul id="l1"><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Terrorism and state threats policy. <span class="p">I oversaw a refresh of the UK’s counter-terrorism strategy, reformed the way we protect ourselves against espionage and foreign interference through the National Security Act and established the Defending Democracy programme. I helped establish new, pro-innovation initiatives to develop the next generation of intelligence collection techniques.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Cyber security. <span class="p">I worked with GCHQ, the NCSC and the NCA to shape the UK’s cyber security policy. I helped develop new powers to seize cryptoassets, change the UK’s approach to ransomware and protect at-risk elected officials and democratic institutions from malicious interference through the Defending Democracy Taskforce.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Investigatory powers policy. <span class="p">I led on reforms to the way that law enforcement and the intelligence services are able to intercept and analyse data through the Investigatory Powers (Amendment) Act. I oversaw changes to the Notices Regime and the use of Internet Connection Records.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Online safety policy. <span class="p">I oversaw the Online Safety Act, and led on the Home Office’s approach to End-to-End Encryption. I was responsible for developing of the Fraud Strategy, and worked with tech companies such as Meta to deliver the first Online Fraud Charter and Global Fraud Summit.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Communications strategy and media appearances. <span class="p">I helped shape the Home Office’s communications strategy, briefed the press and accompanied Ministers on challenging broadcast rounds. I was responsible for strategic comms on sensitive national security issues.</span></p><p class="s3" style="padding-top: 10pt;padding-left: 3pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Special Adviser <span style=" color: #7F7F7F;">Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy</span></p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 3pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">I served as a Special Adviser to the Secretary of State for Business. I was responsible for:</p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Science, innovation and growth policy<span class="p">. I oversaw a policy portfolio that included R&amp;D strategy, technology strategy and security, life sciences, artificial intelligence, quantum technology, the UK space programme and energy including nuclear fusion.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Key policy implementation and critical project delivery<span class="p">. I helped shape and stress-test Horizon Plan B and oversaw interim arrangements for Horizon, Copernicus and Euratom. I helped develop a more strategic approach to R&amp;D investment and a new pro-innovation approach to regulating AI. I worked to ensure that the National Quantum Strategy delivers a strategic advantage for the UK.</span></p><p class="s3" style="padding-top: 7pt;padding-left: 4pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Special Adviser <span style=" color: #7F7F7F;">Department of Health and Social Care</span></p><p style="padding-top: 1pt;padding-left: 4pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">I served as a Special Adviser to the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care. I was responsible for:</p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 13pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Leading on the Health and Care Bill<span class="p">. Considered to be the most significant health legislation for a decade and one of the most challenging Bills of the Parliament. During its passage I quadrupled our majority on charging reform, resisted several ‘genocide amendments’ and developed what was described as the ‘most significant advance in supply chain regulation since the Modern Slavery Act’.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 13pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Policy development<span class="p">. I oversaw a policy portfolio that included capital projects, adult social care, major diseases, life sciences and clinical negligence, working with other advisers to help develop the Secretary of State’s reform agenda. I led on the Union and DHSC’s work with the DAs.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 13pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Policy delivery<span class="p">. I was responsible for implementing flagship policies such as social care charging reform. I was tasked with finding a politically acceptable method of mitigating the risks that the policy posed to the sustainability of care markets and convincing hostile stakeholders of our approach.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 13pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: justify;">Drafting speeches, op eds and social media content<span class="p">. This included political speeches at Party Conference, ministerial statements, and urgent questions and op eds for national media outlets. I also drafted and cleared copy for the Secretary of State’s social media channels.</span></p></li><li data-list-text="•"><p class="s4" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 13pt;text-indent: -9pt;text-align: left;">Working with Members of Parliament on local health and care issues<span class="p">. I helped secure favourable outcomes to health and care issues in MPs’ local areas. These included capital projects, reconfigurations, negotiations and sensitive issues such as local investigations.</span></p></li></ul><h2 style="padding-top: 10pt;padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">Education  <span class="s5">University of Sheffield                   </span><span class="s6">(2013-2016)</span></h2><p class="s7" style="padding-left: 93pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 12pt;text-align: left;">BSc Biomedical Science (Neuroscience) (2:1)</p><h4 style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 92pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">National University of Singapore             <span style=" color: #404040;">(2014-2015)</span></h4><p class="s7" style="padding-left: 92pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">BSc Biomedical Science (Neuroscience) (68)</p><h4 style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 92pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Monkton Combe Senior School              <span style=" color: #404040;">(2008-2012)</span></h4><p class="s9" style="padding-top: 2pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: right;">GCSE:</p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 10pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">7<b>A*</b></p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 10pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">3<b>A</b></p><p class="s8" style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 16pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">A-Level:</p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 13pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">AS Maths: <b>A</b></p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 13pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Physics:  <b>A</b></p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 8pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Biology:  <b>A</b></p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 8pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Chemistry: <b>B</b></p></body></html>
